what
In relay bidding where the partner has shown their hand type, we use a form of RKC, but we nail the trump at the same time as we ask aces.

     3nt is to play. However, the Malay can continue with good unreported values.
     4 ♦ is a stop relay. We want to turn off in an exit. The Malaysian offers 4 ♥, but may offer other things with good unreported values.
     Step 1 (in addition to the above) is RKC in the longest color of the Malay.
     Step 2 is RKC in the second longest suit.
     Step 3 is RKC in the second shortest color.
     Step 4 is RKC in the shortest color.

If two colors are equal in length, the highest color is considered to be "the longest". If the Malay has an unknown length in a number of colors, these are considered to have the same length.

If the distribution-showing final bid was 4 ♦ or higher (unusual), then the stop relay is not available, 4nt ace question with the longest suit is the trump card.
